CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 8, 1964, pg. 22, reads: "Old and New - Everyone was all smiles at the Hilton Hotel last Saturday as former Pittsburgh Pirates First Baseman Dick Stuart talked things over with his replacement, Donn Clendennon, [Clendenon] and Bus. Manager Danny Murtaugh.  Despite many of the controversial stories that have centered around Stuart and Clendennon [sic] since the former Bucco was traded to the Boston Red Sox, the two have remained good friends. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball players Dick Stuart, Donn Clendenon, and manager Danny Murtaugh, in Hilton Hotel for Dapper Dan banquet
